@startuml
title Statlord Dashboard - Control Flow Sequence Diagram

actor User
participant "Browser\n(React Client)" as Client
participant "Redux Store" as Redux
participant "API Layer\n(api.ts)" as API
participant "Django Server\n(DRF)" as Server
participant "Database\n(PostgreSQL)" as DB
participant "Display Device\n(RPi/Arduino)" as Display
participant "Data Source\n(Mock Script)" as DataSource

== Display Registration ==
Display -> Server: POST /api/displays\n(resolution, device_info)
activate Server
Server -> DB: Save Display Configuration
activate DB
DB --> Server: Display ID
deactivate DB
Server --> Display: Display Registered (ID)
deactivate Server

== Dashboard Creation ==
User -> Client: Open Editor
activate Client
Client -> Redux: Dispatch INIT_EDITOR
activate Redux
Redux --> Client: Editor State
deactivate Redux

Client -> API: GET /api/gauges
activate API
API -> Server: Fetch Gauges
activate Server
Server -> DB: Query Gauges
activate DB
DB --> Server: Gauges Data
deactivate DB
Server --> API: JSON Response
deactivate Server
API --> Client: Gauges List
deactivate API

Client -> Redux: Dispatch UPDATE_GAUGES
activate Redux
Redux --> Client: Updated State
deactivate Redux

User -> Client: Add Gauge to Canvas\n(Fabric.js)
Client -> Redux: Dispatch ADD_ELEMENT
activate Redux
Redux --> Client: Canvas Updated
deactivate Redux

User -> Client: Save Layout
Client -> API: POST /api/layouts\n(elements, display_id)
activate API
API -> Server: Create Layout
activate Server
Server -> DB: Save Layout Definition
activate DB
DB --> Server: Layout ID
deactivate DB
Server --> API: Layout Created
deactivate Server
API --> Client: Success Response
deactivate API

Client -> Redux: Dispatch LAYOUT_SAVED
activate Redux
Redux --> Client: State Updated
deactivate Redux
deactivate Client

== Data Update Flow ==
DataSource -> Server: POST /api/gauges/{id}/update\n(value, timestamp)
activate Server
Server -> DB: Update Gauge Value
activate DB
DB --> Server: Updated
deactivate DB
Server --> DataSource: Acknowledged
deactivate Server

== Display Rendering (Polling) ==
Display -> Server: GET /api/displays/{id}/layout
activate Server
Server -> DB: Fetch Display Layout
activate DB
DB --> Server: Layout Configuration
deactivate DB
Server --> Display: Layout Data (JSON)
deactivate Server

Display -> Server: GET /api/gauges\n(poll for updates)
activate Server
Server -> DB: Query Current Values
activate DB
DB --> Server: Gauge Values
deactivate DB
Server --> Display: Current Data
deactivate Server

Display -> Display: Render to Device\n(e-paper/OLED/LCD)

== Viewer Access ==
User -> Client: Open Viewer (/{display_id})
activate Client
Client -> API: GET /api/displays/{id}
activate API
API -> Server: Fetch Display Config
activate Server
Server -> DB: Query Display & Layout
activate DB
DB --> Server: Display Data
deactivate DB
Server --> API: Display Configuration
deactivate Server
API --> Client: Display Info
deactivate API

Client -> Redux: Dispatch LOAD_VIEWER
activate Redux
Redux --> Client: Viewer State
deactivate Redux

loop Data Polling
    Client -> API: GET /api/gauges
    activate API
    API -> Server: Fetch Current Values
    activate Server
    Server -> DB: Query Gauges
    activate DB
    DB --> Server: Latest Values
    deactivate DB
    Server --> API: Gauge Data
    deactivate Server
    API --> Client: Updated Values
    deactivate API

    Client -> Redux: Dispatch UPDATE_VALUES
    activate Redux
    Redux --> Client: Re-render Components
    deactivate Redux
end

deactivate Client

== Server-Side Rendering (Optional) ==
Server -> Server: Invoke Puppeteer\n(serverSideRenderer.js)
activate Server
Server -> Client: Load Viewer in Headless Browser
activate Client
Client -> Client: Render Canvas
Client --> Server: Screenshot/Bitmap
deactivate Client
Server -> Display: Push Rendered Image
deactivate Server

@enduml
